$ waitfor.exe

*Send a signal over a network and wait*

`waitfor.exe` can be used in a → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cmd_exe/batch-files[cmd.exe batch file] to sleep for specified amount of time (although it's probably not intended for that). The `/t` options specifies
the duration in seconds:
code {
C:\> waitfor nul /t 5 2>nul
code }

sa:
  → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/timeout_exe[`timeout.exe`]
